<title>USA: Alexion gets FDA okay for clinical trial.</title>
<headline>Alexion gets FDA okay for clinical trial.</headline>
<dateline>NEW HAVEN, Conn. 1996-09-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Alexion Pharmaceuticals Inc said on Thursday the U.S. Food and Drug Administration cleared it to begin its second clinical trial of its lead drug candidate, the C5 Inhibitor 5G1.1-SC.</p>
<p>The recombinant C5 Inhibitor will be administered to patients undergoing open heart surgery.</p>
<p>The purpose of the Phase I/II trial trial is to accumulate clinical data regarding the drug's safety profile and biological effects in the targeted patient population, the company said. The drug is designed to rapidly penetrate tissue and limit inflammation.</p>
<p>--New York Newsdesk, 212-859-1733</p>
</text>
